          "ruleId": "tachi/stride/spoofing",
          "message": {
            "text": "An attacker could spoof the End User identity at session establishment, submitting User Turn requests under a victim user's identity if authentication on the inbound HTTPS surface relies solely on weak or single-factor credentials. The persistent persona state in the Conversation Session Store amplifies this risk. [Control: missing]"
